<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <title>Site Settings</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/style.css">
</head>
<body>
  <div class="admin-bar">
    <span>‚öôÔ∏è Site Settings</span>
    <div>
      <a href="/admin/dashboard">Dashboard</a>
      <a href="/">View Site</a>
      <a href="/admin/logout">Logout</a>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="container" style="padding: 40px;">
    <h1 style="margin-bottom: 30px;">Site Settings</h1>
    
    <div class="admin-controls">
      <h3>Customize Colors</h3>
      <p style="margin-bottom: 20px; color: var(--secondary-text);">
        Use the color pickers below to customize your site's appearance. The header and sidebar will automatically be 10% lighter than your background color for a pleasing contrast.
      </p>
      
      <form id="settingsForm">
        <div class="form-group">
          <label>Background Color</label>
          <p style="font-size: 13px; color: var(--secondary-text); margin-bottom: 8px;">Main page background color (header/sidebar will be automatically lightened)</p>
          <input type="color" id="backgroundColor" value="<%= settings.backgroundColor %>">
        </div>
        
        <div class="form-group">
          <label>Post Background</label>
          <p style="font-size: 13px; color: var(--secondary-text); margin-bottom: 8px;">Background color for blog post cards</p>
          <input type="color" id="postBackground" value="<%= settings.postBackground %>">
        </div>
        
        <div class="form-group">
          <label>Text Color</label>
          <p style="font-size: 13px; color: var(--secondary-text); margin-bottom: 8px;">Main text color throughout the site</p>
          <input type="color" id="textColor" value="<%= settings.textColor %>">
        </div>
        
        <button type="submit">Save Settings</button>
      </form>
      
      <div style="margin-top: 30px; padding: 20px; background: #fff3cd; border: 1px solid #ffc107; border-radius: 6px;">
        <strong>üí° Tip:</strong> The header and sidebar automatically use a color 10% lighter than your background for a cohesive look. Just pick one background color and the rest is handled for you!
      </div>
      
      <div style="margin-top: 20px; padding: 20px; background: #e7f3ff; border: 1px solid #0d6efd; border-radius: 6px;">
        <strong>Preview:</strong> Visit the <a href="/" target="_blank">main site</a> in a new tab to see your changes after saving.
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <script src="/script.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
